transcript.text: Hello everyone, welcome to this tutorial on how to create kit products in on Print Shop.
Kit products allow you to bundle multiple items into a single package.
Whether you're offering promotional packages or customized sets, On Print Shop makes it easy to create and manage these kit products.
Let's get started.
The On Print Shop system allows its admins to create kit products from the predefined products and offer those to their end customers.
Let's check out the front store first.
Here you can find 3 products, a card holder, a sports bag and AT shirt with options to enter their quantity, select size, color, customization, etcetera.
With the Including Kit check box, the customer can remove any product from the kit.
To include all the products from the kit, they simply need to check they include all items in order checkbox from the top.
We have a setting in the admin panel to enable this feature.
On the right hand side we have the kit summary where you can verify the pricing and enter or select the total quantity of the kit based on the setting before proceeding with the checkout.
Here is how you can create such a kit product.
From the on Print Shop admin panel, navigate to the Product section and go to the Predefined Products page.
Click on the Add button.
Enter the name of the kit product such as Office Supply.
Select a product category and move to the primary setting Kit Product as discussed in our Predefined Products tutorial video.
This setting allows you to define if you want to create a Kit product, where selecting NO will enable you to only create a predefined product.
Buy with Kit only allows you to create a complete kit product and YES allows you to create a product where the customers can add previously created predefined product as a kit.
When you select Buy with Kit only, you have all the options similar to what you have while creating predefined products.
So in this video we are selecting YES to explore the other features and functionalities.
After selecting yes, click on Save.
You can define the description for this product and images and then continue to the Kit Products tab.
Here you will get the list of all the predefined products from the system.
You can assign the selected products to create a kit layout.
Show Fields enables the admin to select the fields to be displayed at the front store for the individual products of the kit at the front store.
We saw that customers can choose the products they want to purchase in the kit.
For that you need to enable the Allow Partial Kit.
If this setting is disabled, then customers need to buy all the products from the kit.
They will not have any option to edit the selection.
With the lock quantity setting, you can restrict the total quantity of the kit in addition to the quantity of individual products.
When enabled, you can enter the numbers for the total kit with, separation and this will be displayed as a drop down in the kit summary section.
If you have any business scenarios where you want to charge your customers additionally for the kit, you can mention that cost in the Additional cost field.
Once done, click on Save.
In the next Kit Product rule screen.
You will get the provision to lock the number of individual items with a default quantity if the Lock quantity setting in the previous screen is disabled.
The Meta Tag tab works similarly to the standard products where you need to enter the details for SEO purposes.
Save all the details and that's it.
You successfully created a kit product.
You can view and manage your kit products from the predefined product list section.
With this icon, you can verify that this is a kit product.
This was all about how you can create and manage kit products and on Print Shop.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
